data.text:
LONDON, Friday.-General Slr Charles

Harington, who was Governor of Gibraltar

1933-8. has died at Cheltenham at the agc of

68. He will be chiefly remembered for his

important work In the Great War as thc

junior partner In the Plumer-Harington com-

bination which won glory in Its command of

thc Second Anny, and by his courage and re-

source during a dangerous situation at

Channk in 1922, when he commanded the Al-

lied Forces at Constantinople.
